                            <comment id="14045104" author="thobbs" created="Thu, 26 Jun 2014 20:19:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;7475.txt avoids the NPE.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14045641" author="slebresne" created="Fri, 27 Jun 2014 07:03:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14046004" author="thobbs" created="Fri, 27 Jun 2014 14:39:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14068366" author="0x6e6562" created="Mon, 21 Jul 2014 09:59:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I can confirm that this fix (as applied to 2.1-rc4) has resolved part of the an issue reported in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-7566&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-7566&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When I run the the TestReprepareStatement test case from the gocql integration suite against the 2.1-rc3 tarball, it fails:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;bool:gocql 0x6e6562$ go test . -v -test.run=TestReprepareStatement
=== RUN TestReprepareStatement
--- FAIL: TestReprepareStatement (0.31 seconds)
	cassandra_test.go:588: Failed to execute query &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; reprepare statement: java.lang.NullPointerException
FAIL
exit status 1
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But when I run it against the 2.1-rc4 tarball, it passes:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;bool:gocql 0x6e6562$ go test . -v -test.run=TestReprepareStatement
=== RUN TestReprepareStatement
--- PASS: TestReprepareStatement (0.25 seconds)
PASS
ok  	github.com/relops/gocql	0.267s
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
